# Quiz Prototype Project

Container-bound Google Apps Script + clasp project for a teacher/student multi-question quiz with Anthropic-powered batch grading, optional per-question images (PNG/GIF), student post-evaluation review, and teacher review with student-comment filtering.

## Files

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `Code.gs` | Server logic: routing, quiz CRUD, images, student submit, AI evaluation, student/teacher review, logging, pilot seeds |
| `teacher.html` | Teacher dashboard — **Add Question**, **Evaluate**, **Review** (`?teach`) |
| `add-question.html` | Spreadsheet modal for **Quiz → Add Question and Rubric** |
| `student.html` | Take quiz + **Review Results** (default `doGet`) |
| `appsscript.json` | V8 runtime, OAuth scopes, web app config |
| `.clasp.json` | Script/spreadsheet IDs for `clasp push` |
| `setup.sh` | Push code + attempt remote `setupSheet` |

## Spreadsheet tabs

- **Questions** — A = row, B = question, C = rubric, D = quiz name, E = quiz ID, F = question ID, G = image (`data:image/...;base64,...` for new saves; legacy `PARTS:n` still supported)
- **QuestionImages** — legacy chunked storage (A = question ID, B = quiz ID, C = part, D = chunk); still read for old `PARTS:n` rows
- **Responses** — A = timestamp, B = name, C = answer, D = status, E = question ID, F = quiz ID (one row per answer)
- **Evaluations** — A = timestamp, B = name, C = answer, D = rubric, E = AI feedback, F = question ID, G = quiz ID, **H = Student Review** (student question/comment after AI evaluation)
- **Logs** — A = timestamp, B = level, C = source, D = message, E = details (JSON)

Questions in the same quiz share **quiz name** (D) and **quiz ID** (E). Each question row has its own **question ID** (F). IDs are random 8-character strings (no ambiguous chars).

## Question images

- **Optional** PNG or GIF via file picker; max **1 MB** file size.
- **Save path (current):** client sends full data URL in `addQuestionAndRubric({ quizName, question, rubric, imageData })` — **one** `google.script.run` call; server validates with `prepareQuestionImageData_` and stores in **Questions column G** (same pattern as the flashcards app).
- **Do not reintroduce transport chunking** unless a proven payload limit is hit; chunking multiplies round trips (~15 s vs ~5 s for typical images).
- **Legacy read path:** `PARTS:n` in G + **QuestionImages** tab still loads via `readQuestionImageDataForQuestion_`.
- **Student:** `getQuestionsForQuiz` returns `hasImage` only (uses `questionHasImageMarker_`); image loaded lazily via `getQuestionImage` + client `imageCache`.
- **Review (teacher + student):** `getEvaluationsForQuiz` returns `hasImage` (not `imageData`); lazy load via `getQuestionImage` + `imageCache`.

## IDs and linking

- Do **not** rely on row numbers to match Questions ↔ Responses ↔ Evaluations.
- Link by **question ID** (+ **quiz ID** when the same question could appear in multiple quizzes).
- `ensureQuestionIds_(questionsSheet)` batch-backfills empty F column.

## End-to-end workflow

1. Teacher creates quiz (questions + rubrics).
2. Students take quiz → Responses (**Pending**).
3. Teacher runs **Evaluate** → AI writes Evaluations column E; Responses → **Complete**.
4. Students open **Review Results** → read AI feedback; optional question/comment saved to Evaluations column H.
5. Teacher opens **Review** → browse all evaluations or **Student Comments Only** to focus on flagged items.

## Teacher workflow

1. **Add Question** — quiz name, question, rubric, optional image; reusing quiz name reuses quiz ID.
2. **Evaluate** — lists **all quizzes** from Questions (not only those with Pending responses). **Evaluate** is disabled when `pendingCount === 0`. Each card shows **last evaluation timing** from Logs (estimated + server actual; client wait when logged). Run grading via `triggerEvaluation(quizId)` (single server call, question-first batching).
3. **Review** — pick a quiz; browse evaluations in a **2×2 grid** (Question | Student Response, Rubric | AI Evaluation) plus a full-width **Student Question or Comment** row below. **Show:** **All Questions** (default) or **Student Comments Only** (client-side filter on `studentReviewText`; disabled when `commentedCount === 0`). **Sort by Student** (default) or **Question** (client-side). Quiz list cards show `evaluatedCount` and `commentedCount`. **Edit Evaluation** → `updateEvaluation`.

Spreadsheet menu: **Quiz → Run AI Evaluation**, **Seed Histogram Pilot Quiz**, **Seed Extended Pilot Quiz**, **Clear all quiz data...**, **Open Logs**, **Authorize API access**, **Set up sheets**.

**Clear all quiz data** deletes all data rows in Questions, Responses, and Evaluations (headers kept). Logs are not cleared. Use before re-seeding pilots.

## Student workflow

1. Open deployment URL (no query string).
2. **Take a Quiz** (default mode): enter name, pick quiz — **one server call** loads all question text/metadata (not images). Answer one question at a time; **Submit Quiz** → Responses, Status **Pending**.
3. **Review Results**: enter name → `getStudentReviewQuizList` shows quizzes with AI evaluations for that student → browse question-by-question (2×2 grid + editable comment row). Comments saved via `updateStudentReview` to Evaluations column H. Auto-save on Previous/Next; **Save Comment** for explicit save.

## URLs

- Student: web app URL (default `doGet`)
- Teacher: same URL + `?teach`

## Deployment checklist

1. `clasp push --force` after code changes
2. **Deploy → Manage deployments** → pencil (edit **existing** deployment) → **New version** → **Deploy** (same URL) — required for **teacher.html** / **student.html** changes; spreadsheet menu picks up `Code.gs` after refresh
3. `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in Script Properties (not in source code)
4. Run **Quiz → Authorize API access** once for `UrlFetchApp`
5. Web app: Execute as **Me**, access **Anyone**

**Verify HTML deploy:** both `student.html` and `teacher.html` show `#buildLabel` at bottom of the card (e.g. `build: 20260629-review-comments`). **Bump the build string** in both files whenever shipping UI changes; tell the user what to look for. Do **not** rely on the left-hand deployment description in Manage deployments — that is the deployment label, not the version note, and may not change when a new version is created.

Anthropic API calls run on **Google's servers**, not the school network.

## Grading (question-first batch, 4-point rubric)

All evaluation uses a **Grading for Equity** 4-point scale (0–4). The philosophy is in `EVAL_GRADING_PHILOSOPHY_` in `Code.gs` and is **included in every** `callAnthropicBatchGrade_` API request:

- **4** — correctly addressed **all** requested facts from the question-specific rubric
- **3** — correctly addressed **most** requested facts
- **2** — correctly addressed **some** requested facts
- **1** — addressed **at least one** requested fact correctly
- **0** — **none** of the requested facts from the rubric

Per-question rubrics (Questions column C) should list **requested facts** and **common misconceptions**, not point buckets out of 10. The global 4-point scale applies on top of those facts.

- Model: `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001` via `triggerEvaluationByQuestion_(quizId)`.
- Groups **Pending** responses by question; sends up to **15 student answers per API call** (`EVAL_BATCH_SIZE_`).
- Model returns JSON array: `[{ id, score, feedback }]` where `id` = Responses row number and `score` is 0–4.
- Writes Evaluations column E as `Score: X/4\n\n{feedback}`.
- Text-only grading (images not sent to model).
- Validated pilots:
  - **Histograms Pilot Quiz** — 5 students × 2 questions = 10 answers, **2 API calls** (~13 s)
  - **Histograms Extended Pilot Quiz** — 16 students × 8 questions = 128 answers, **16 API calls** (~71–80 s server)

## Evaluation timing (planning + troubleshooting)

- **Estimate:** `3 s` overhead + `5 s` per Anthropic API call (`EVAL_ESTIMATE_SEC_OVERHEAD_`, `EVAL_ESTIMATE_SEC_PER_API_CALL_`), calibrated from pilots.
- **Logs** (linked by `evalRunId`):
  - Source `evaluation`, `evaluationTiming` — `started` / `completed` / `failed` with `estimatedSec`, `actualSec`, `deltaSec`, `deltaPct`, counts
  - Source `evaluationUi` — server payloads (`serverResultReady`, `evaluateListLoaded`)
  - Source `teacherEvaluate` — client UI events via `logFromClient` (`finishEvaluationUi`, `client timing reported`, etc.)
- **Teacher Evaluate cards:** `getQuizEvaluationList()` attaches `lastEvaluation` per quiz from latest completed log row (no age cutoff). Returned via `serializeQuizEvaluationListForClient_` (primitives only — **no Date objects**).
- **Hybrid UI timing:** server **estimate** from `triggerEvaluation` result; **client wait time** measured in browser; completion overlay requires **OK** to dismiss.

## UI feedback

All web pages use a **processing overlay** (`showProcessing` / `showDone` / `hideProcessing` / `dismissProcessing`) during async server calls. After evaluation, **Done** shows a checkmark and **OK** button (user must dismiss); quiz list reloads on OK.

## Question content (for demos)

- Write question, rubric, and sample answers as **single paragraphs** (no line breaks in sheet cells).
- Prefer rubrics that list **requested facts** and **named misconceptions**; scoring uses the global 0–4 scale above, not per-fact point weights.
- `seedHistogramPilotQuiz()` — 2 questions, 5 students (10 responses).
- `seedExtendedHistogramPilotQuiz()` — 8 questions, 16 students (128 responses); delete existing extended quiz rows before re-seeding.

## Roadmap

- **Statistics content:** histogram pilots seeded; expand question bank as needed.
- **Future teacher features:** create/copy/archive/delete quiz (not implemented).
- **Future grading:** optional vision input for questions with images; auto-resume Evaluate after 6-minute GAS timeout.
